    "Table 8 shows the results of the evaluation, i.e.",
    "how the images were classified (real or synthetic).",
    "Our evaluation shows that training segmentation networks with synthetic images works well, with Dice scores that reach 91%-100% compared to when training with real images (for BraTS 2021 and 2020, respectively).",
    "Shin et al.",
    "24 obtained a relative Dice score of 77.6% for brain tumor segmentation, using the deep convolutional GAN architecture which is older than progressive GAN."
